To generate a random 2D array of size `m x n` in MATLAB, find the maximum value along with its indices, and modify the code to find the top `k` maximum values and their corresponding indices, you can follow the steps below.

### MATLAB Code

1. **Generate a Random 2D Array and Find Maximum Value:**

```matlab
% Define the size of the array
m = 5; % number of rows
n = 4; % number of columns

% Generate a random 2D array
A = rand(m, n);

% Find the maximum value and its indices
[maxValue, linearInd] = max(A(:));
[row, col] = ind2sub(size(A), linearInd);

% Display the results
fprintf('Maximum Value: %.4f\n', maxValue);
fprintf('Row Index: %d\n', row);
fprintf('Column Index: %d\n', col);
```

2. **Modify the Code to Find the Top `k` Maximum Values:**

```matlab
% Define the number of top maximum values needed
k = 3;

% Flatten the matrix and sort it in descending order
[sortedValues, sortedIndices] = sort(A(:), 'descend');

% Get the top k values and their linear indices
topKValues = sortedValues(1:k);
topKIndices = sortedIndices(1:k);

% Convert linear indices to row and column indices
[topKRows, topKCols] = ind2sub(size(A), topKIndices);

% Display the top k maximum values and their indices
fprintf('Top %d Maximum Values and their Indices:\n', k);
for i = 1:k
    fprintf('Value: %.4f, Row: %d, Column: %d\n', topKValues(i), topKRows(i), topKCols(i));
end
```

### HTML Code to Display the Results

To display the results in a simple HTML webpage, you can use the following code:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Random 2D Array Results</title>
    <style>
        table {
            width: 50%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
            margin: 20px auto;
        }
        th, td {
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            padding: 8px;
            text-align: center;
        }
        th {
            background-color: #f2f2f2;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1 style="text-align: center;">Random 2D Array Results</h1>
    <table>
        <tr>
            <th>Value</th>
            <th>Row Index</th>
            <th>Column Index</th>
        </tr>
        <!-- Repeat this <tr> block for each maximum value -->
        <tr>
            <td>0.8765</td>
            <td>2</td>
            <td>3</td>
        </tr>
        <!-- Add more rows as needed for top k values -->
    </table>
</body>
</html>
```

### How to Use the HTML Code

- Replace the placeholder values (`0.8765`, `2`, `3`, etc.) in the `<tr>` block with the actual results you obtained from MATLAB.
- Repeat the `<tr>` block for each of the top `k` values you want to display.

By following these steps, you can generate a random 2D array in MATLAB, find the maximum values and their indices, and display the results on a webpage using HTML.
